20book%20came%20three%20years%20after%20former%20President%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson%20signed%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%20of%201964%2C%20making%20it%20illegal%20to%20discriminate%20based%20on%20race%2C%20color%2C%20sex%2C%20religion%2C%20or%20national%20origin.%20It%20was%20a%20time%20of%20widespread%20social%20unrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%2C%20King%20sought%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20address%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eways%20for%20the%20community%20to%20move%20forward%20together%2C%20including%20addressing%20issues%20like%20poverty%20through%20a%20guaranteed%20annual%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e89ac63b-8dca-47f5-a2c2-ce736b715ac0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMLK%20Jr.%20wrote%20that%20a%20guaranteed%20income%20could%20help%20address%20social%20issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226389%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696a9839c58df2ecd5ccb3ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224308%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMartin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20suggested%20implementing%20a%20guaranteed%20annual%20income.%3Cp%3EVernon%20Merritt%20III%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%2C%20King%20wrote%20that%20proposing%20such%20an%20idea%20in%20the%20early%201900s%20%26quot%3Bwould%20have%20been%20greeted%20with%20ridicule%20and%20denunciation%20as%20destructive%20of%20initiative%20and%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20little%20has%20changed%20a%20century%20later.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-politics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopponents%20of%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20programs%20still%20argue%20that%20the%20cash%20will%20dissuade%20workers%20from%20working.%20Numerous%20studies%2C%20however%2C%20have%20shown%20that%20recipients%20don't%20work%20less%20and%20often%20use%20the%20cash%20to%20find%20better%20work%20by%20taking%20classes%20and%20upskilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20that%20time%2C%20economic%20status%20was%20considered%20the%20measure%20of%20the%20individual's%20abilities%20and%20talents.%20And%20in%20the%20thinking%20of%20that%20day%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20worldly%20goods%20indicated%20a%20want%20of%20industrious%20habits%20and%20moral%20fiber%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20come%20a%20long%20way%20in%20our%20understanding%20of%20human%20motivation%20and%20of%20the%20blind%20operation%20of%20our%20economic%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKing%20wrote%20that%20shifts%20in%20the%20economy%20and%20discrimination%20can%20push%20people%20toward%20%26quot%3Bconstant%20or%20frequent%20unemployment%20against%20their%20will.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20Americans%20must%20either%20create%20employment%20opportunities%20or%20create%20income%20so%20people%20can%20become%20active%20consumers.%20Unemployed%20citizens%20could%20take%20on%20jobs%20focused%20on%20boosting%20social%20good%2C%20King%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20guaranteed%20income%20program%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20could%20help%20address%20social%20ills%20and%20improve%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20our%20nation%20can%20spend%20thirty-five%20billion%20dollars%20a%20year%20to%20fight%20an%20unjust%2C%20evil%20war%20in%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20twenty%20billion%20dollars%20to%20put%20a%20man%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20it%20can%20spend%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20put%20God's%20children%20on%20their%20own%20two%20feet%20right%20here%20on%20earth%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225e20051-11bc-4f0f-83a8-6f31ae4276d6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20basic%20income%20stands%20today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20nearly%2060%20years%20since%20%26quot%3BWhere%20Do%20We%20Go%20From%20Here%3F%26quot%3B%20was%20published%2C%20basic%20income%20programs%20have%20remained%20a%20divisive%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnologists%20like%20Musk%2C%20Altman%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Gates%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0believe%20some%20form%20of%20basic%20income%20will%20be%20necessary%20when%20AI%20is%20so%20smart%20it%20can%20do%20most%20anyone's%20jobs%2C%20including%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20handful%20of%20politicians%20have%20also%20advocated%20for%20basic%20income%20programs.%20A%20group%20of%20lawmakers%20last%20year%20proposed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-monthly-basic-income-program-bill-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enationwide%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20pilot%20program%20spanning%20three%20years%20and%2010%2C000%20Americans.%20The%20monthly%20payments%20would%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20a%202-bedroom%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIncreasing%20automation%20and%20advancing%20AI%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20expand%20human%20flourishing.%20However%2C%20the%20concentration%20of%20control%20of%20those%20technologies%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20few%20billionaires%20may%20mean%20the%20eventual%20loss%20of%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20millions%20of%20Americans%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawmakers%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224814%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrew%20Yang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696d3c0ea645d1188187922c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223209%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Yang%20has%20advocated%20for%20a%20universal%20basic%20income.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEntrepreneur%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-yangs-on-universal-basic-income-versus-higher-wages-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Yang%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0also%20pushed%20for%20a%20univer