e%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%2C%20an%20independent%20agency%20with%20a%20single%20director%2C%20could%20have%20its%20leader%20fired%20by%20the%20president%20%26quot%3Bat%20will%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20for%20any%20reason%20whatsoever%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bfor%20cause.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20suggested%20it%20may%20soon%20allow%20%26quot%3Bat%20will%26quot%3B%20firings%20of%20leaders%20of%20independent%20agencies%20led%20by%20multi-member%20boards%2C%20too.%20In%20December%2C%20it%20heard%20oral%20arguments%20for%20a%20lawsuit%20brought%20by%20Rebecca%20Slaughter%2C%20who%20Trump%20fired%20from%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20letter%20firing%20Slaughter%20didn't%20identify%20any%20cause%2C%20even%20though%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20previously%20said%20presidents%20need%20to%20meet%20that%20standard%20to%20remove%20FTC%20commissioners.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flisa-cook-firing-federal-reserve-board-tro-decision-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunlike%20Cook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20allowed%20Slaughter%20to%20be%20removed%20from%20her%20post%20while%20additional%20legal%20proceedings%20play%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223872%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22rebecca%20slaughter%20ftc%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696956bb764ca5f34d2a8ab7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222581%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERevecca%20Slaughter%20sued%20to%20keep%20her%20job%20as%20an%20FTC%20commissioner%20after%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20fired%20her.%3Cp%3ESalwan%20Georges%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20hasn't%20yet%20issued%20a%20final%20ruling%20in%20Slaughter's%20case.%20But%20during%20oral%20arguments%20in%20December%2C%20several%20Republican-appointed%20justices%20indicated%20they%20could%20deal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-case-humphrey-fed-independence-lisa-cook-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20death%20blow%20to%20a%2090-year-old%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20recognized%20limits%20to%20the%20president's%20ability%20to%20fire%20members%20of%20independent%20agencies.%20The%20landmark%20unanimous%20ruling%20said%20agencies%20like%20the%20FTC%20were%20%26quot%3Bquasi-judicial%20and%20quasi-legislative%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20structure%20intended%20to%20safeguard%20them%20from%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20domination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20John%20Roberts%20referred%20to%20the%201935%20opinion%2C%20known%20as%20Humphrey's%20Executor%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20dried%20husk.%26quot%3B%20Justices%20Neil%20Gorsuch%20and%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%20both%20asked%20Slaughter's%20lawyer%20if%20he%20could%20cite%20different%20Supreme%20Court%20precedents%20that%20would%20allow%20her%20to%20keep%20her%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20past%20year's%20legal%20battles%20between%20the%20Trump%20administration%20and%20independent%20agency%20leaders%2C%20the%20justices%20have%20gone%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20single%20out%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20justices%20allowed%20Trump%20to%20remove%20members%20from%20two%20independent%20agencies%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Merit%20Systems%20Protection%20Board%20and%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20%E2%80%94%20but%20said%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20%26quot%3Bfor%20cause%20removal%20protections%26quot%3B%20would%20need%20to%20be%20considered%20with%20its%20%26quot%3Bdistinct%20historical%20tradition%26quot%3B%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20a%20uniquely%20structured%2C%20quasi-private%20entity%20that%20follows%20in%20the%20distinct%20historical%20tradition%20of%20the%20First%20and%20Second%20Banks%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20justices%20wrote%20in%20an%20unsigned%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustice%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%20took%20pains%20during%20oral%20arguments%20in%20the%20Slaughter%20case%20to%20indicate%20that%20he%20was%20inclined%20to%20give%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20special%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20questioning%20Solicitor%20General%20John%20Sauer%2C%20Kavanaugh%20asked%20about%20drawing%20%26quot%3Ba%20principled%2C%20sensible%20line%26quot%3B%20that%20would%20distinguish%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20from%20other%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20other%20side%20says%20that%20your%20position%20would%20undermine%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20and%20they%20have%20concerns%20about%20that%2C%20and%20I%20share%20those%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20Kavanaugh%20told%20Sauer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22279a3741-b62c-4b5e-be96-00daa131a250%5C%22%3EThe%20stakes%20for%20the%20American%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20most%20Americans%20don't%20interact%20with%20the%20Fed%20directly%2C%20its%20policies%20affect%20their%20everyday%20lives.%20By%20controlling%20the%20direction%20of%20interest%20rates%2C%20the%20central%20bank%20determines%20the%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20and%20returns%20on%20savings.%20The%20Fed%20and%20its%20independence%20are%20the%20cornerstones%20of%20the%20dollar's%20status%20as%20the%20world's%20reserve%20currency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20hear%20Cook's%20lawyers%20and%20prominent%20economists%20tell%20it%2C%20the%20potential%20damage%20is%20extraordinarily%20high.%20If%20Trump%20can%20fire%20her%2C%20then%20the%20door%20is%20open%20for%20future%20presidents%20to%20steamroll%20the%20Fed%20and%20cause%20economic%20chaos%2C%20they%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20think%20about%20the%20Cook%20removal%20as%20seeking%20a%20roadmap%20from%20the%20court%20for%20how%20to%20potentially%20remove%20other%20governors%2C%20including%20Jerome%20Powell%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lev%20Menand%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20administrative%20law%20and%20financial%20institutions%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225847%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20standing%20next%20to%20Jerome%20Powell%20on%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20Fed's%20renovated%20office%20buildings%2C%20pointing%20to%20a%20sheet%20of%20paper%20in%20Powell's%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6967c30b764ca5f34d2a6ccb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223898%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Justice%20Department's%20probe%20into%20Powell%20relates%20to%20the%20Fed%20Chair's%20testimony%20about%20central%20bank%20renovations%20last%20year.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20attempt%20to%20fire%20Cook%2C%20Trump%20cited%20a%20criminal%20referral%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-bill-pulte-housing-lisa-cook-federal-reserve-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Pulte%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Finance%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20said%20Cook%20lied%20on%20mortgage%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20apparent%20deceitfulness%2C%20according%20to%20Trump%2C%20made%20Cook%20ill-suited%20for%20her%20role%20in%20setting%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20public%20indication%20that%2C%20in%20the%20months%20since%20Pulte's%20letter%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20has%20opened%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20into%20Cook's%20mortgage%20paperwork.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20maintained%20that%20the%20president%20can%20fire%20a%20Federal%20Reserve%20board%20member%20for%20any%20reason%20and%20that%20courts%20don't%20have%20the%20power%20to%20second-guess%20any%20%26quot%3Bfor%20cause%26quot%3B%20justifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook's%20attorneys%20argue%20that%20such%20freedom%20defeats%20the%20entire%20purpose%20of%20%26quot%3Bfo