C%22%5C%22%3ECopper%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20up%20sharply%2C%20breaking%20above%20%2412%2C000%20a%20ton%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20last%20week%20and%20rising%20more%20than%2040%25%20in%2012%20months.%20The%20AI%20buildout%20is%20one%20factor%20that's%20sent%20demand%20soaring.%20However%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcopper-price-record-high-demand-supply-prediction-ai-data-centers-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20a%20study%20by%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20month%20said%20that%20supply%20will%20fall%20massively%20short%20between%20now%20and%202040%2C%20barring%20a%20sizable%20increase%20in%20production.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20predicts%20that%20copper%20production%20will%20peak%20in%202030%2C%20leaving%20the%20world%20roughly%2010%20million%20metric%20tons%20short%20by%202040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pebble%20Mine%20project%20sits%20on%20vast%20copper%20and%20gold%20reserves.%20However%2C%20its%20operations%20have%20been%20blocked%20since%202014%20under%20an%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20provision%20that%20has%20remained%20in%20place%20across%20the%20Obama%2C%20Biden%2C%20and%20Trump%20administrations.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPebble%20is%20a%20world-class%20deposit%2C%26quot%3B%20Deantha%20Skibinski%2C%20who%20serves%20as%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Alaska%20Miners%20Association%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20copper%20in%20the%20ground%20at%20the%20pebble%20project%20is%20immense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20there%20are%20few%20copper%20producers%20in%20the%20US%20with%20the%20type%20of%20reserves%20that%20Pebble%20Mine%20is%20sitting%20on.%20The%20project's%20owner%20says%20the%20site%20is%20the%20world's%20largest%20undeveloped%20store%20of%20both%20copper%20and%20gold.%20It%20also%20has%20large%20deposits%20of%20molybdenum%20and%20silver%2C%20two%20metals%20that%20also%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20AI%20buildout.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkibinski%20recalled%20the%20EPA's%202014%20decision%20to%20block%20the%20mine%20during%20its%20exploratory%20phase%20after%20it%20failed%20a%20watershed%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20did%2C%20which%20we%20contend%20is%20not%20legal%2C%20is%20that%20they%20issued%20the%20404(c)%20veto%20preemptively%2C%20meaning%20before%20the%20company%20went%20into%20permitting%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20is%20unprecedented.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPebble%20Limited%20responded%20with%20a%20lawsuit%2C%20kicking%20off%20a%20long%2C%20complicated%20legal%20saga.%20More%20than%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20the%20mine%20is%20still%20not%20in%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20the%20US%20under%20Trump%20scrambles%20to%20secure%20domestic%20supplies%20of%20critical%20materials%2C%20Skibinski%20thinks%20the%20Pebble%20Mine%20project%20should%20get%20another%20look%20by%20the%20administration.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20think%20that%20the%20government%20should%20fully%20examine%2C%20transparently%20and%20honestly%2C%20how%20to%20get%20more%20mines%20that%20produce%20copper%20and%20other%20minerals%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20you%20talk%20about%20what%20it%20actually%20takes%2C%20there%20are%20many%20that%20say%20they're%20not%20interested%20in%20going%20that%20route.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Ffact-sheets%2F2025%2F10%2Ffact-sheet-president-donald-j-trump-approves-ambler-road-project-to-unlock-alaskas-mineral-potential%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpressed%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20other%20Alaska%20mining%20endeavors%20during%20his%20first%20term%2C%20including%20the%20Pebble%20Mine%20and%20a%20project%20that%20would%20open%20up%20the%20state's%20mineral-rich%20Ambler%20Mining%20District.%20But%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F08%2F05%2