%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-work-from-home-jobs-persisting-fewer-new-roles-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20from%20home%20more%20frequently%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20their%20company's%20official%20policy%20permits.%20He%20believes%20many%20of%20these%20arrangements%20are%20%26quot%3Boff%20the%20record%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20granted%20by%20individual%20managers%20without%20formal%20company%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%20said%20one%20reason%20some%20managers%20might%20allow%20these%20exceptions%20is%20that%20they're%20often%20evaluated%20based%20on%20their%20team's%20performance.%20If%20a%20manager%20is%20concerned%20that%20top%20employees%20will%20quit%20or%20become%20less%20productive%20under%20stricter%20in-office%20requirements%2C%20they%20may%20decide%20to%20offer%20more%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManagers%20are%20allowing%20employees%20extra%20days%20at%20home%20because%20they%20are%20high%20performers%20or%20hard%20to%20replace%20in%20their%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BManagers%20ultimately%20care%20about%20their%20team%20performance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20these%20off-the-record%20exceptions%20was%20granted%20to%20a%20Wisconsin-based%20mother%20of%20three%20who%20works%20in%20a%20corporate%20role%20at%20a%20manufacturing%20company.%20When%20her%20employer%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-mom-gave-up-250k-income-avoiding-rto-policy-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive-day-a-week%20in-office%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%2C%20she%20worried%20a%20two-hour%20round-trip%20commute%20would%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20manage%20her%20childcare%20responsibilities.%20After%20an%20%26quot%3Boff-the-record%26quot%3B%20conversation%20with%20her%20manager%2C%20she%20was%20told%20that%20as%20long%20as%20she%20came%20in%20a%20few%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20for%20key%20in-person%20meetings%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wouldn't%20give%20her%20any%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20need%20to%20work%20from%20home%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20whether%20it's%20work%20or%20personal%20reasons%2C%20then%20that's%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22995e711c-3b26-4af1-8def-0ed7f95a4c82%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20WFH%20flexibility%20is%20out%20in%20the%20open%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20every%20work-from-home%20exception%20is%20off%20the%20record.%20After%20struggling%20to%20make%20it%20into%20the%20office%20following%20day%20care%20drop-off%2C%20Georg%20Loewen%2C%20a%20senior%20director%20of%20digital%20marketing%20at%20a%20public%20relations%20agency%2C%20said%20his%20manager%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-manager-commuting-return-office-day-care-childcare-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformally%20exempted%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20time%20being%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20company's%20three-day-a-week%20in-office%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20drop-off%20ran%20long%20or%20parking%20didn't%20work%20out%2C%20I'd%20just%20work%20from%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Loewen%2C%20who's%20in%20his%2030s%20and%20lives%20in%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoewen%20said%20he%20sometimes%20worries%20about%20how%20his%20arrangement%20might%20be%20perceived%20by%20coworkers%20who%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20flexibility%2C%20but%20that%20he%20has%20consistently%20felt%20supported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222019%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Georg%20Loewen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69694880764ca5f34d2a8854%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221514%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGeorg%20Loewen%3Cp%3EGeorg%20Loewen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%20said%20he%20often%20hears%20about%20West%20Coast%20employees%20who%20are%20granted%20additional%20work-from-home%